des. White blood cells migrate from blood to connective tissue in response to certain immune system conditions.</span></span></div></div><div class="sfnudnq" data-testid="set-page-term-card-side"><div class="sumuxuf"><div class="hm80q9a h1ql76m6"><span class="TermText notranslate lang-en">Name and describe the types of cells commonly found in connective tissue.</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div aria-label="Term" class="SetPageTermsList-term"><div class="slnuhr5"><div class="a11nf743"><button type="button" aria-label="Star" class="bvbv8re a1qd8xfe aj47u34 ayaxb5p AssemblyIconButton AssemblyButtonBaseV2 AssemblyButtonBaseV2--medium" data-testid="assembly-icon-button-text-secondary" title="Star" style="--button-height: 2.5rem; --content-opacity: 1;"><span class="cz3acib n17nrlic"><svg aria-label="star filled" class="AssemblyIcon AssemblyIcon--medium" role="img"><noscript></noscript><use xlink:href="#star-filled"></use><noscript></noscript></svg></span></button><div class="t1vey32f"><div tabindex="-1" class="fu3v3nt" data-testid="AssemblyTooltip--base"><button type="button" aria-label="Audio" class="bvbv8re a1qd8xfe aj47u34 ayaxb5p AssemblyIconButton AssemblyButtonBaseV2 AssemblyButtonBaseV2--medium" data-testid="assembly-icon-button-text-secondary" title="Audio" style="--button-height: 2.5rem; --content-opacity: 1;"><span class="cz3acib n17nrlic"><svg aria-label="sound" class="AssemblyIcon AssemblyIcon--medium" role="img"><noscript></noscript><use xlink:href="#audio"></use><noscript></noscript></svg></span></button></div></div></div><div class="sewpbju" style="--sewpbju-0: 0rem;"><div class="szwq4v1" style="--szwq4v1-0: 40% minmax(0, 1fr);"><div class="sfnudnq" data-testid="set-page-term-card-side"><div class="sumuxuf"><div class="s1rpwius h1ql76m6"><span class="TermText notranslate lang-en">A and C</span></div></div></div><div class="sfnudnq" data-testid="set-page-term-card-side"><div class="sumuxuf"><div class="hm80q9a h1ql76m6"><span class="TermTe